Branch.description:
This class represents a branch adn therefore includes lines, cables or branch fuses.

It is characterized by a branch type (line, cable or fuse).
Branch.title: Branch

ExternalGrid.description:
This class represents an external grid or a grid subsitute equivalent respectively.

It is characterized by a grid type (slack, P-V-node, P-Q-node).
ExternalGrid.title: ExternalGrid

Load.description:
This class represents a load.

It is mainly characterized by the load model of active and reactive power, the connected phases and the load type itself (Producer, Consumer, Storage or passive shunt).
Load.title: Load

LoadModel.description:
Load representation based on polynomial model.

power = power_0*(c_p*(U/U_0)^exp_p + c_i*(U/U_0)^exp_i + (c_z)*(U/U_0)^exp_z)
c_z = 1 - c_p - c_i
LoadModel.title: LoadModel

Meta.description: This class represents the meta data related to the grid export.
Meta.title: Meta

Node.description: This class represents a terminal within the grid.
Node.title: Node

PhaseAngleClock.description: Phase shift between two windings in multiples of 30°.
PhaseAngleClock.title: PhaseAngleClock

PhaseConnections.description: Phases between which elements are connected, e.g. [(A,E). (B,E). (C,E)], [(A,B), (B,C), (C,A)].
PhaseConnections.title: PhaseConnections

RatedPower.description:
Rated power of a load specified by rated apparent power and power factor.

A RatedPower object should be created via the class method "from_apparent_power(apparent_power, power_factor)"
as active and reactive power will be automatically computed based on rated power and powerfactor.
RatedPower.title: RatedPower

Transformer.description:
This class represents a transformer and consists of winding elements.

It is characterized by windings elements (2w or 3w), the vector group as well as the transformer tap control.
Transformer.title: Transformer

Winding.description:
This class represents a winding of a transformer.

For example, a 2-winding transformer has a high and low voltage level winding.
Each windings is characterized by vector group, which defines the interconnection of the three phases.
Winding.title: Winding

description:
This class represents operating point independent topology of a grid.

It is characterized by list of branches, nodes, loads, transformers and external grids.
title: Topology
